headline.main: CATHOLIC WOMEN HEAR MASS TODAY; 175 New Members of Charity Group to Be Admitted at Annual Service BREAKFAST WILL FOLLOW Episcopalian Group Formed Here to Cooperate in Aiding European Refugees

lead_paragraph: One hundred seventy-five women will become members of the Ladies of Catholic Charity at the annual mass of that organization at 9 A.M. today in St. Patrick's Cathedral. Bishop Stephen J. Donahue will be the celebrant and the Rev. Vincent J. Brosnan, moderator of the group, the headquarters of which are at 415 Lexington Avenue, will assist him.
